        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Pantlludw, Machynlleth.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>March 15<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>.</date>
                    <salute>Dear M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Darwin</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am very sorry that I am unable to tell you anything about the ledges, as hitherto we have failed to discover any appearance of what you describe— The steep slopes here are perfectly smooth, &amp; it is difficult to imagine any change taking place in them, as worm-casting are rarely to be seen on the hills.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>Thanking you for your letter I am | Your’s sincerely | Amy Ruck</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="annotations">
                <note><hi rend="italic">Top of letter</hi>: ‘(Worms)’ <hi rend="italic">blue crayon</hi></note>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8224.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to Amy Ruck, 24 February [1872]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD had asked for a drawing of ledges that might have been formed by the washing down of worm-castings (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8224.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to Amy Ruck, 24 February [1872]</ref>).</note>
